title: Grateful Dead Live at Jai-Alai Fronton on 1974-06-22
lineage: AKG D-1000E mics > Sony 152 deck (Maxell UD-120's) >
description:
Set 1: Promised > Bertha > Greatest, Deal, Bobby McGee, Scarlet, Jack Straw, Loose Lucy, Mexicali, Sugaree, Race Is On, Roses, Playin

Set 2: China Cat Sunflower > I Know You Rider, Me & My Uncle, Ship Of Fools, El Paso, Eyes of the World > Wharf Rat > Sugar Magnolia 

Encore: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: What A Great Show!! The Energy Cooks!! Excellent Set Lists; very well played.  Very Good Sound Quality -- Better than many audience tapes I've heard.  Take a Listen and you'll agree: this is well worth the Dowload.  Peace and Love.
hot show their just on fire, i just got finished listenin to greatest story ever told and it was the hottest version i've ever heard, i cant wait to listen to the rest.

Wow! I was going to write an eloquent teview but I just listened to China Cat Sunflower and all I can say now is... Wow... Wow.

Wow!

Ok, I've recovered enough to say: this is some of the most flowing, creative and just plain beautiful playing I've ever heard. Oh, and the rest of this show is great, too. For those who like Wharf Rat, like me, this one's special!

Great sound, too. Well done, Wiz. OK, so the drums are a little low but, boy, do those guitars sound good.
sweet This show is just pure sweetness.Probably the best from 74.Amazing setlist with some good sound.Wish i was there that night to dance my worries away.5 stars all the way.

just unbelieveable hello, I've been listening to the dead for 20 years (im 34) and the older I get the more I love them - just makes me cry hearing this set it is so wonderful.
thankyou all so much for recording these shows and posting them here, it's amazing to hear all this pure gold sound from the greatest band in the world.
not that great I disagree with most of the comments about this being "unreal".   It's kind of a flat performance to me.   They sound bored.

quesnay Had to weigh in on this show. Simply amazing. It's been over thirty years since I flew down to Miami to catch the dead at the only small venue they played with the exception of Winterland. The China-Rider was one of those China/Riders where you felt as though you were like Jodie Foster in Contact, traveling to the center of the galaxy. Thinking about this show still gives me goose bumps.
Playin' Most of playing unlistenable and disturbing ....don't see the point
